  35. let clear q =
  36.   q.length <- 0;
  37.   q.first <- Nil;
  38.   q.last <- Nil

  40. let add x q =
  41.   let cell = Cons {
  42.     content = x;
  43.     next = Nil
  44.   } in
  45.   match q.last with
  46.   | Nil ->
  47.     q.length <- 1;
  48.     q.first <- cell;
  49.     q.last <- cell
  50.   | Cons last ->
  51.     q.length <- q.length + 1;
  52.     last.next <- cell;
  53.     q.last <- cell

  55. let push =
  56.   add

  58. let peek q =
  59.   match q.first with
  60.   | Nil -> raise Empty
  61.   | Cons { content } -> content

  63. let peek_opt q =
  64.   match q.first with
  65.   | Nil -> None

  68. let top =

  71. let take q =
  72.   match q.first with
  73.   | Nil -> raise Empty
  74.   | Cons { content; next = Nil } ->
  75.     clear q;
  76.     content
  77.   | Cons { content; next } ->
  78.     q.length <- q.length - 1;

  80.     content

  82. let take_opt q =

  93. let pop =

  96. let copy =
  97.   let rec copy q_res prev cell =
  98.     match cell with
  99.     | Nil -> q_res.last <- prev; q_res
  100.     | Cons { content; next } ->
  101.       let res = Cons { content; next = Nil } in
  102.       begin match prev with
  103.       | Nil -> q_res.first <- res
  104.       | Cons p -> p.next <- res
  105.       end;
  106.       copy q_res res next
  107.   in
  108.   fun q -> copy { length = q.length; first = Nil; last = Nil } Nil q.first

  118.     match cell with
  119.     | Nil -> ()
  120.     | Cons { content; next } ->
  121.       f content;

  126. ‌let fold =
  127.   let rec fold f accu cell =
  128.     match cell with
  129.     | Nil -> accu
  130.     | Cons { content; next } ->
  131.       let accu = f accu content in
  132.       fold f accu next
  133.   in
  134.   fun f accu q -> fold f accu q.first

  136. ‌let transfer q1 q2 =
  137.   if q1.length > 0 then
  138.     match q2.last with
  139.     | Nil ->
  140.       q2.length <- q1.length;
  141.       q2.first <- q1.first;
  142.       q2.last <- q1.last;
  143.       clear q1
  144.     | Cons last ->
  145.       q2.length <- q2.length + q1.length;
  146.       last.next <- q1.first;
  147.       q2.last <- q1.last;
  148.       clear q1
